<Author>Moche
<Content>Very Nice Hotel We loved so much about this hotel: nice rooms, great rainshower, water and apples, pleasant staff. And the restaurant was so good, we ate there two nights after sightseeing all day, especially nice to have somewhere so close to go to when you are exhausted. But I have to say, check in was not fun. We got a new, inexperienced person who didn't quite know what he was doing. He had no idea where the parking was located, couldn't find the cards and no one else in the place seemed to know either. So my husband had to park the car on the street, couldn't find anything and finally after he managed to find a space, he lost his way back. I was waiting and worrying for a half hour. Not something you want to endure when you are checking in at 9pm. I can forgive an inexperienced person, but the staff person who corresponded with me by email while booking the room was just plain inept. I specifically asked in advance about parking and was told that it was available, I just had to ask when I got there. He mentioned nothing about a charge, so I figured this meant they had their own parking and it was free. Not true. The real situation is that they have an affiliation with a parking garage nearby that charges 17.50 EUR a day. Or, if that is full, there is another across the street that charges 20 EUR a day. if I had known this ahead of time, I may have found a hotel with better parking, but since he didn't tell me, I ended up tacking on 52 EUR to my bill. How hard is it to tell guests about parking? Staff answering the reservation requests need to brush up on the basic knowledge of the facilities of the hotel. 
