<Content>What a disapointment! Was very excited to stay at this hotel after visiting their website.Unfortunately I didn't read all the reviews about the hotel because otherwise I would have chosen a different option.I must say, all negative comments about the hotel are true!The staff aren't too friendly although for a change, they spoke in English. We walked through the restaurant to the elevator and had to take a second elevator to the 3rd floor, which is in the old part of the building. The lifts are tiny!!! And made in the early 1900's! Scary to go in! Didn't enjoy dragging our heavy luggage through 2 lifts with no help. Never seen anything like this!Needed to use our room key to access the 3rd floor becuase it still has old residences living there. The building is not only the hotel!Our double room was literally across the door which accesses the 3rd floor. Because it's an old building (renovated of course) the doors old and slammed everytime someone went through it, and every door on the floor on the floor could be heared when going in and out. You could here people walking, talking, showering....The worse part about it is that our room faced the small passage way of the hotel, not the street and I was startled at 4 am by loud strange noises for a few hours straight. Turns out that the Food Market across the street stores and transports their products through this passage. I heard bottles being poured into a dumpster, carts being wheeled very loudly down the passage, drunk men spitting, yelling...It was aweful! When I went to change the room in the morning, they said we have the quietest room in the hotel because it doesn't face the street. I said to myself, if this is the quietest, I wonder how loud the other rooms are! To top off the noise probem ,Market seems to be rennovating and perhaps putting in a a new elevator shaft for the whole hotel to access. THat's great! BUT the noise at 8:30, 9:00 am is terrible. This goes on all day until late evening.Last comment in about the decor. At first is seems very nice but in our room we felt s crammed and the furniture and room's setup was poor. If you know what feng shui is, then this had such poor feng shui. Not good vibes here at all!. Mybe depends on the room. But do not get a room on the 3rd floor (ours was 304) and perhaps the suites are better set up. Looks like first floor (with noise from the street) would be your best bet.Food was good but the whole experience wasn't great!A disappointment - the owner really missed the point! Their other hotel in palamos was WONDERFUL!! Hotel Trias! How could the same owner mess up the hotel in Barca? 
