<Content>Thoroughly enjoyed my stay I don't usually write reviews---most hotels have nothing noteworthy to mention, but the Market Hotel caught my spirit and is a great value. I moved here after spending three nights at a Hilton while I was on business. I found it curiously attractive (hard to find, multiple lifts for 3 floors, frosted windows with views to utilitarian courtyards).The hotel is modern and located in a building where the upper floors are under renovation (maybe it's noisy during the day, but who stays in their room in Barca?). There are all the amenities that you need and plenty of extras (breakfast buffet included, cooler with water and apples). The staff was pleasant, attentive, helpful and attractive. The room was large and clean, with wooden floors. I had two comfortable double beds. There was a flat-screen television and a computer connection (a computer was available for guest use). The bathroom was roomy, clean and functional ---I don't know which I liked better the large one-piece stone wash basin, or the tiled shower that actually had the right combination of pressure and volume. The body wash and shampoo smelled great and there was a hair dryer that I didn't use. It's somewhat difficult to find but worth the search (both on the internet and in person. I can't say enough about its restaurant---great food, high quality and low price. The hotel is located close-in near the Mercat St. Antoni, a wonderful place to spend an hour (or more) if you are at all interested in local food, culture, language, etc. The metro is a block away, cabs are available on call or on the street (within a minute or two, but spotty). 5-10 minute walk to La Rambla. 
