<Content>Excellent boutique hotel The hotel was a great place to stay, at a very good price. We stayed in a standard double and a junior suite and found each to be good-sized rooms, very nicely decorated. The staff was uniformly courteous and helpful. The included breakfast was nothing special (fruit danish and bread were good, coffee and ensaimada were not), so we ended up skipping it half the mornings. The rooms aren't very sound proofed, though, so I could imagine an unpleasant experience if you ended up with loud neighbors (we could hear people talking, but that wasn't too bad). And, as a minor point, I would liked there to have been mattress covers on the beds, rather than what felt like just sheets on the mattresses. Overall, though, we had an excellent experience and would definitely recommend the hotel. 
